content: Once the Complete & Submit button is clicked in the opened form copy, it is moved to the Complete folder.

comment.text: This translation key is used to describe the action of submitting a form. It will be displayed as a tip or guidance message in a UI element, likely next to a "Complete & Submit" button. Its purpose is to inform users about what happens when they click this button, specifically moving the form copy to the "Complete" folder.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Arabic translation includes quotation marks around "إكمال وإرسال" and "مكتمل". While quotation marks are used in Arabic, their usage here seems unnecessary and might hinder readability. It's best to align with the English style of not using quotes.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Remove the quotation marks around "إكمال وإرسال" and "مكتمل": بمجرد الضغط على زر إكمال وإرسال في نسخة النموذج، يتم نقلها إلى مجلد مكتمل.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation "Tamamlanmış qovluğuna köçürülür" doesn't perfectly capture the nuance of 'moved to the Complete folder'. It implies a transfer or migration rather than a placement within a folder.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Açılan forma nüsxəsində Tamamla və Göndər düyməsini sıxdıqda, 'Tamam' qovluğuna yerləşdirilir.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: While not a severe issue, maintaining consistency in casing might be beneficial. 'Tamam' and 'Göndər' could potentially be capitalized consistently throughout the interface or documentation.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider capitalizing 'Tamam' and 'Göndər' consistently.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The English phrase 'Complete & Submit' is translated as 'Completa e Invia'. While not strictly incorrect, 'Invia' (send) might imply an action beyond simply marking the form as complete. 'Completa' alone is a more accurate representation of the intended meaning within this context.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Completa e Salva

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The phrase 'questa viene spostata' is grammatically correct but slightly awkward. It could be improved for smoother reading.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: viene spostata nella cartella Completati

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Japanese translation uses katakana for 'Complete & Submit'. While acceptable, using a more natural Japanese equivalent like 「完了送信」 might be more user-friendly and consistent with other UI elements.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider replacing 「完了＆送信」 with 「完了送信」.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Korean translation uses a direct translation of "Complete & Submit" which doesn't flow naturally in Korean. It would be more idiomatic to use a term that encapsulates both actions.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider using a phrase like "제출 및 완료" (jeomcheol mit malwo) or "완료 제출" (wanlyo jeomcheol) to replace "완료 & 제출".

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Lao translation uses quotation marks that may not be standard Lao. Consider using a more common Lao quotation mark style.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Review and potentially adjust quotation mark style to align with Lao conventions (e.g., using guillemets «»).

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation includes quotes around 'Pabeigtas'. While acceptable, it's more common in Latvian to omit the quotes for folder names in instructional text. It's not a critical error, but improves readability.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Remove the quotes around 'Pabeigtas'.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The phrase "Complete & Submit" is not accurately reflected in the Polish translation. "Zakończ i prześlij" is a literal translation but may not convey the intended meaning within the context of form submission. A more natural phrasing might be needed.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider alternatives like "Wyślij i Zakończ" or "Zatwierdź i Wyślij", or research common phrasing used for submitting forms in Polish UI contexts.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The phrase "Gotowe" is capitalized. While technically acceptable, it might be stylistically better to be lowercase ("gotowe") to maintain consistency with other labels.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Change "Gotowe" to "gotowe".

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'Concluir & Enviar' is a direct translation of 'Complete & Submit' but might not be the most natural phrasing in Portuguese. A more common and natural way to express 'Complete & Submit' would be 'Finalizar & Enviar' or 'Concluir e Enviar'.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Finalizar & Enviar

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The phrase 'este é movido' is passive voice and a bit clunky in Portuguese. A more natural wording would be active.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: ele é movido

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The word 'Concluído' is likely intended to be 'Concluir'. 'Concluído' means 'completed,' whereas the original English refers to the action of completing and submitting.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Depois que o botão Concluir e Enviar for clicado na cópia do formulário aberto, ele será movido para a pasta de Formulários Concluídos.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The English phrase "Complete & Submit" is directly translated to "Completare și trimitere". While technically correct, it's less natural in Romanian. A more common and user-friendly equivalent would be "Finalizare și trimitere" or "Închidere și trimitere".
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider translating "Complete & Submit" as "Finalizare și trimitere" or "Închidere și trimitere".

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The English phrase 'moved to the Complete folder' is translated as 'mutat în folderul Formulare completate'. While understandable, 'Formulare completate' is a bit clunky. A more natural phrasing would be something like 'în folderul Completate' or 'în folderul Finalizate'.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider translating 'moved to the Complete folder' as 'în folderul Completate' or 'în folderul Finalizate'.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The quotation marks used for button names are Russian style (« ») which may not be consistent with the rest of the UI and might look out of place.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider using standard English quotation marks ("") or a UI consistent quotation style for button names to maintain a uniform look and feel. Alternatively, clarify whether Russian style quotes are intentionally used for localization purposes.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The phrase "Complete & Submit" is not accurately translated. "සම්පූර්ණ කර ඉදිරිපත් කරන්න" translates to 'complete and submit', but lacks the nuance of a button label. It could be misinterpreted as a general instruction rather than a button title.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider a more literal translation of 'Complete & Submit' that maintains the button-like feel, such as "සම්පූර්ණකොට ඉදිරිපත් කරන්න" or exploring alternatives that reflect the action of pressing a button in Sinhala.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The word "ෆෝල්ඩරයට" (folderaya) appears to be a correct spelling, but the double 'l' in 'folder' is a consistent point of error. It's recommended to confirm consistency with standard Sinhala orthography. The spelling is acceptable but worth checking for consistency.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Double-check the correct spelling of 'folder' with a Sinhala dictionary or a native speaker to ensure it aligns with established orthographic conventions. While technically correct, consistency matters.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation 'Dokončaj in oddaj' is a literal translation of 'Complete & Submit' which might not be the most natural phrasing in Slovenian. 'Dokončaj in pošljite' or 'Dokončaj in oddaj' would be more idiomatic, though the provided version isn't technically incorrect.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider 'Dokončaj in pošljite' or 'Dokončaj in oddaj' for a more natural flow.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: While technically correct, 'se ta premakne' is slightly awkward. It would be more fluid to say 'premakne se'.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Change 'se ta premakne' to 'premakne se'.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Serbian translation uses a lowercase 'к' in 'кликане' which should be uppercase 'К' to match the capitalization of the English 'clicked'.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Када се Кликане на дугме Заврши и пошаљи у отвореној копији формулара, он се премешта у фолдер Завршено.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The Ukrainian translation uses quotation marks (« ») for the button name, which might not be the standard practice in Ukrainian UI/UX. Consider using single quotes (').
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Change «Завершити та надіслати» to 'Завершити та надіслати'

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The ampersand (&) in the original English content is represented as a space in the Vietnamese translation. While understandable, it's better to replace it with 'và' for consistency and clarity.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Khi nút Hoàn thành và Gửi trên bản sao biểu mẫu đã mở được nhấp vào, nó sẽ được chuyển đến thư mục Hoàn thành.

ai_spell_check_issues.description: The translation uses quotation marks for 'Complete & Submit' and 'Complete' folder. The English original uses the same.
ai_spell_check_issues.suggestion: Consider maintaining consistency in quotation mark usage or avoiding quotation marks entirely based on the overall style guide.
